thread.title: RBNZ’s Wheeler Says Further Easing Likely, Supporting Economy
thread.title_full: RBNZ’s Wheeler Says Further Easing Likely, Supporting Economy - Bloomberg Business

author: Matthew Brockett
title: RBNZ’s Wheeler Says Further Easing Likely, Supporting Economy
text:
Reserve Bank of New Zealand Governor Graeme Wheeler said while futher monetary policy easing is likely, there are several factors supporting economic growth.
“Some local commentators have predicted large declines in interest rates over coming months that could only be consistent with the economy moving into recession,” Wheeler said in a speech in Tauranga published on the RBNZ’s website Wednesday. “At this point, we believe that several factors are supporting economic growth.”
